If that's the case, here's a direct .NET translation of that Gradle workflow, keeping the same job breakdown (build + dependency submission) but using setup-dotnet, NuGet caching, and the Microsoft dependency submission toolkit for .NET:

```yaml
# .github/workflows/dotnet-ci-gradle-style.yml
name: .NET CI (matching Gradle workflow style)

on:
  push:
    branches: [ "main" ]
  pull_request:
    branches: [ "main" ]

jobs:
  build:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    permissions:
      contents: read
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - name: Setup .NET
        uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4
        with:
          dotnet-version: '8.0.x'            # change to your target framework
      - name: Cache NuGet packages
        uses: actions/cache@v4
        with:
          path: ~/.nuget/packages
          key: ${{ runner.os }}-nuget-${{ hashFiles('**/*.csproj', '**/*.vbproj') }}
          restore-keys: |
            ${{ runner.os }}-nuget-
      - name: Restore dependencies
        run: dotnet restore
      - name: Build
        run: dotnet build --no-restore --configuration Release
      - name: Test
        run: dotnet test --no-build --configuration Release --verbosity normal

  dependency-submission:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    permissions:
      contents: write
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - name: Setup .NET
        uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4
        with:
          dotnet-version: '8.0.x'
      - name: Submit dependencies to GitHub dependency graph
        uses: microsoft/dependency-submission-toolkit@v1
        with:
          project-files: |
            ./src/**/*.csproj
```

---

🧠 What this does

· build job – restores, builds, and tests your .NET project, with NuGet caching (just like the Gradle wrapper cache).
· dependency-submission job – runs the official .NET dependency submission toolkit, which populates your repo’s dependency graph (used for Dependabot alerts and SBOM). This mirrors the Gradle dependency-submission functionality but for NuGet/Proprietary packages.

