Patch (replace the "Get changed changelog files" step in .github/workflows/release-note-changes.yml with the contents below)

```name=.github/workflows/release-note-changes.yml url=https://github.com/Kaki-blue-com/firebase-android-sdk/blob/595165f2dd6f61c7f939c4d51b3fa5ab758a9c1b/.github/workflows/release-note-changes.yml
      - name: Get changed changelog files
        id: changed-files
        run: |
          git diff --name-only "${{ github.event.pull_request.base.sha }}" "${{ github.event.pull_request.head.sha }}" > /tmp/all_changed_files.txt
          grep CHANGELOG.md /tmp/all_changed_files.txt > /tmp/changelog_file_list.txt || true
          if [[ -s /tmp/changelog_file_list.txt ]]; then
            echo "any_changed=true" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT
          else
            echo "any_changed=false" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT
          fi
          echo "all_changed_files=$(cat /tmp/changelog_file_list.txt)" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT
          rm /tmp/all_changed_files.txt /tmp/changelog_file_list.txt
```

Why this works
- grep ... || true prevents a non-zero exit code from aborting the step.
- [[ -s file ]] checks whether the changelog list is non-empty so any_changed is set correctly.
- The step always completes and provides outputs for later conditional steps.

